verbose_text: The finding that TF Ag levels are unaltered by food intake contrasts observations described by Motton et al. XREF_BIBR However, postprandial blood samples in that study were drawn 3.5 and 6 hours following a standardized 40% fat meal that induced an increase in mean TG concentration by over 100% (3.5 hours postprandial), whereas the mean postprandial increase in TG concentration in our study confined itself to 22%.
